21/05/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A total of 48 people were detained on Thursday (May 20th) in a large-scale operation against organised crime, drug trafficking and weapons smuggling that spanned several towns. Republika Srpska Interior Minister Stanislav Cadjo said police seized large amounts of drugs, weapons and munitions. Prosecutors describe it as one of the largest joint anti-crime actions by police services of the two entities. (RTRS, BHRT, Nezavisne Novine - 20/05/10)
